  "prompt": "Can we know if our card has been inserted in ATM?",
  "response": "Yes, you can generally know if your card has been inserted into an ATM. While using an ATM, the machine typically provides feedback through its screen and sometimes through sounds (like beeps) when a card is successfully inserted. Here are some common indications:\n\n1. **Screen Prompts:** After inserting your card, the ATM will display instructions on the screen, such as asking you to enter your PIN.\n\n2. **Card Release:** If the card is not correctly inserted or is malfunctioning, the ATM might display an error message and may eject the card.\n\n3. **Visual Indicators:** Some ATMs have a light indicator that shows the status of the card insertion.\n\n4. **Operating Sounds:** Many ATMs will make a sound when the card is successfully accepted.\n\nIf you are unsure whether your card has been properly inserted, you can usually check these indicators or simply reinsert the card following the instructions on the screen. If you think there is a problem (for example, the ATM has captured your card without returning it), it is best to contact your bank or the ATM operator immediately for assistance.",
